description:
While our previous ride provided us a clean separated bike path, no such path is available here. The plan here is to wind our way through the major metropolitan area of Kobe, scrambling between sidewalks, main roads, alleyways, and pedestrian bridges.

Once we make our way out the other side of the city, we are rewarded with views of golden beaches and azure seas, eventually passing under the Akashi-Kaikyo Bridge - which was the world's longest suspension bridge until March 2022.
